.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-HEALTH" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-health \- single-call node health snapshot
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-health
.SH DESCRIPTION
Returns a compact JSON health snapshot for quick operator diagnostics:
.nf
{ok, daemon, block_height, num_channels, balanced,
 pending_htlcs, warnings:[]}
.fi
.TP
.B ok
.B true
when the daemon is reachable, synced, and no warnings are present.
.TP
.B daemon
.B true
when
.BR lightning-cli (1)
can reach the daemon.
.TP
.B block_height
Current best block known to the daemon, or
.B null
when unreachable.
.TP
.B num_channels
Number of active (CHANNELD_NORMAL or CHANNELD_AWAITING_LOCKIN) channels.
.TP
.B balanced
.B false
when any active channel has less than 10 % of its capacity on the local
side.
.TP
.B pending_htlcs
Total in-flight HTLCs across all channels.
.TP
.B warnings
Array of diagnostic strings; empty when healthy.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always (use the
.B ok
field to detect problems).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-node-info (1),
.BR lightning-node-log (1),
.BR lightning-wallet-check (1)
